              "textContents": [
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "Reported speech",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    "Read the rules and complete the example sentences with the correct form of the verbs."
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "When we report what people say or report their thoughts or ideas, we use a reporting verb (said, told, asked) and we usually change the tense of the verb(s) in the sentence (simple present -> simple past, present progressive -> past progressive, will -> would)."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    ""
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "• 65 percent of people said they had a preferred news website.",
                    "• The survey asked how often people checked the news.",
                    "• Most people said they would think more carefully about the news stories."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    ""
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "We also do this when we report someone’s words directly. We also change the pronoun (I -> he/she, you -> me)"
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    ""
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "‘Do you like your job?’ -> She asked me if I liked my job."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 5,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    ""
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "‘I’m doing some work.’ -> He said he was doing some work."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 6,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    ""
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "‘I don’t think there’s a lot of fake news.’ -> She said she didn't think there was a lot of fake news."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 7,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [
                    ""
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "I’ll get back to you later.’ -> He said he would get back to me later."
                  ]
                }
              ],
